Harry watched the girl and her mother disappear as the train rounded the corner. Houses flashed past the window. Harry felt a great leap of excitement. He didn\rquote t know what he was going to \emdash  but it had to be better than what he was leaving behind.\par
The door of the compartment slid open and the youngest red\-headed boy came in.\par
\ldblquote Anyone sitting there?\rdblquote  he asked, pointing at the seat opposite Harry. \ldblquote Everywhere else is full.\rdblquote\par
Harry shook his head and the boy sat down. He glanced at Harry and then looked quickly out of the window, pretending he hadn\rquote t looked. Harry saw he still had a black mark on his nose.\par
\ldblquote Hey, Ron.\rdblquote\par
The twins were back.\par
\ldblquote Listen, we\rquote re going down the middle of the train \emdash  Lee Jor\-dan\rquote s got a giant tarantula down there.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Right,\rdblquote  mumbled Ron.\par
\ldblquote Harry,\rdblquote  said the other twin, \ldblquote did we introduce ourselves? Fred and George Weasley. And this is Ron, our brother. See you later, then.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Bye,\rdblquote  said Harry and Ron. The twins slid the compartment door shut behind them.\par
\ldblquote Are you really Harry Potter?\rdblquote  Ron blurted out.\par
Harry nodded.\par
\ldblquote Oh \emdash  well, I thought it might be one of Fred and George\rquote s jokes,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote And have you really got \emdash  you know \'85\rdblquote\par
He pointed at Harry\rquote s forehead.\par
Harry pulled back his bangs to show the lightning scar. Ron stared.\par
\ldblquote So that\rquote s where You-Know-Who \emdash  ?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote but I can\rquote t remember it.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Nothing?\rdblquote  said Ron eagerly.\par
\ldblquote Well \emdash  I remember a lot of green light, but nothing else.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Wow,\rdblquote  said Ron. He sat and stared at Harry for a few moments, then, as though he had suddenly realized what he was doing, he looked quickly out of the window again.\par
\ldblquote Are all your family wizards?\rdblquote  asked Harry, who found Ron just as interesting as Ron found him.\par
\ldblquote Er \emdash  yes, I think so,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote I think Mom\rquote s got a second cousin who\rquote s an accountant, but we never talk about him.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote So you must know loads of magic already.\rdblquote\par
The Weasleys were clearly one of those old wizarding families the pale boy in Diagon Alley had talked about.\par
\ldblquote I heard you went to live with Muggles,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote What are they like?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Horrible \emdash  well, not all of them. My aunt and uncle and cousin are, though. Wish I\rquote d had three wizard brothers.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Five,\rdblquote  said Ron. For some reason, he was looking gloomy. \ldblquote I\rquote m the sixth in our family to go to Hogwarts. You could say I\rquote ve got a lot to live up to. Bill and Charlie have already left \emdash  Bill was head boy and Charlie was captain of Quidditch. Now Percy\rquote s a prefect. Fred and George mess around a lot, but they still get really good marks and everyone thinks they\rquote re really funny. Everyone expects me to do as well as the others, but if I do, it\rquote s no big deal, because they did it first. You never get anything new, either, with five broth\-ers. I\rquote ve got Bill\rquote s old robes, Charlie\rquote s old wand, and Percy\rquote s old rat.\rdblquote\par
Ron reached inside his jacket and pulled out a fat gray rat, which was asleep.\par
\ldblquote His name\rquote s Scabbers and he\rquote s useless, he hardly ever wakes up. Percy got an owl from my dad for being made a prefect, but they couldn\rquote t aff\emdash  I mean, I got Scabbers instead.\rdblquote\par
Ron\rquote s ears went pink. He seemed to think he\rquote d said too much, because he went back to staring out of the window.\par
Harry didn\rquote t think there was anything wrong with not being able to afford an owl. After all, he\rquote d never had any money in his life until a month ago, and he told Ron so, all about having to wear Dudley\rquote s old clothes and never getting proper birthday presents. This seemed to cheer Ron up.\par
\ldblquote\'85 and until Hagrid told me, I didn\rquote t know anything about be\-ing a wizard or about my parents or Voldemort \emdash\rdblquote\par
Ron gasped.\par
\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\i\ldblquote You said You-Know-Who\rquote s name!\rdblquote\i0  said Ron, sounding both shocked and impressed. \ldblquote I\rquote d have thought you, of all people \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I\rquote m not trying to be \i brave\i0  or anything, saying the name,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote I just never knew you shouldn\rquote t. See what I mean? I\rquote ve got loads to learn. \'85 I bet,\rdblquote  he added, voicing for the first time some\-thing that had been worrying him a lot lately, \ldblquote I bet I\rquote m the worst in the class.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote You won\rquote t be. There\rquote s loads of people who come from Muggle families and they learn quick enough.\rdblquote\par
While they had been talking, the train had carried them out of London. Now they were speeding past fields full of cows and sheep. They were quiet for a time, watching the fields and lanes flick past.\par
Around half past twelve there was a great clattering outside in the corridor and a smiling, dimpled woman slid back their door and said, \ldblquote Anything off the cart, dears?\rdblquote\par
Harry, who hadn\rquote t had any breakfast, leapt to his feet, but Ron\rquote s ears went pink again and he muttered that he\rquote d brought sand\-wiches. Harry went out into the corridor.\par
He had never had any money for candy with the Dursleys, and now that he had pockets rattling with gold and silver he was ready to buy as many Mars Bars as he could carry \emdash  but the woman didn\rquote t have Mars Bars. What she did have were Bertie Bott\rquote s Every Flavor Beans, Drooble\rquote s Best Blowing Gum, Chocolate Frogs, Pumpkin Pasties, Cauldron Cakes, Licorice Wands, and a number of other strange things Harry had never seen in his life. Not want\-ing to miss anything, he got some of everything and paid the woman eleven silver Sickles and seven bronze Knuts.\par
Ron stared as Harry brought it all back in to the compartment and tipped it onto an empty seat.\par
\ldblquote Hungry, are you?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Starving,\rdblquote  said Harry, taking a large bite out of a pumpkin pasty.\par
Ron had taken out a lumpy package and unwrapped it. There were four sandwiches inside. He pulled one of them apart and said, \ldblquote She always forgets I don\rquote t like corned beef.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Swap you for one of these,\rdblquote  said Harry, holding up a pasty. \ldblquote Go on \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote You don\rquote t want this, it\rquote s all dry,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote She hasn\rquote t got much time,\rdblquote  he added quickly, \ldblquote you know, with five of us.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Go on, have a pasty,\rdblquote  said Harry, who had never had any\-thing to share before or, indeed, anyone to share it with. It was a nice feeling, sitting there with Ron, eating their way through all Harry\rquote s pasties, cakes, and candies (the sandwiches lay for\-gotten).\par
\ldblquote What are these?\rdblquote  Harry asked Ron, holding up a pack of Chocolate Frogs. \ldblquote They\rquote re not \i really\i0  frogs, are they?\rdblquote  He was start\-ing to feel that nothing would surprise him.\par
\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote But see what the card is. I\rquote m missing Agrippa.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Oh, of course, you wouldn\rquote t know \emdash  Chocolate Frogs have cards inside them, you know, to collect \emdash  famous witches and wizards. I\rquote ve got about five hundred, but I haven\rquote t got Agrippa or Ptolemy.\rdblquote\par
Harry unwrapped his Chocolate Frog and picked up the card. It showed a man\rquote s face. He wore half-moon glasses, had a long, crooked nose, and flowing silver hair, beard, and mustache. Under\-neath the picture was the name Albus Dumbledore.\par
\ldblquote So \i this\i0  is Dumbledore!\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\ldblquote Don\rquote t tell me you\rquote d never heard of Dumbledore!\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Can I have a frog? I might get Agrippa \emdash  thanks \emdash\rdblquote\par
Harry turned over his card and read:\par
