\pard\nowidctlpar\li567\ri567\qj Considered by many the greatest wizard of modern times, Dumbledore is particularly famous for his defeat of the Dark wizard Grindelwald in 1945, for the discovery of the twelve uses of dragon\rquote s blood, and his work on alchemy with his partner, Nicolas Flamel. Professor Dumbledore enjoys chamber music and tenpin bowling.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\qj Harry turned the card back over and saw, to his astonishment, that Dumbledore\rquote s face had disappeared.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\ldblquote He\rquote s gone!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Well, you can\rquote t expect him to hang around all day,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote He\rquote ll be back. No, I\rquote ve got Morgana again and I\rquote ve got about six of her \'85 do you want it? You can start collecting.\rdblquote\par
Ron\rquote s eyes strayed to the pile of Chocolate Frogs waiting to be unwrapped.\par
\ldblquote Help yourself,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote But in, you know, the Muggle world, people just stay put in photos.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Do they? What, they don\rquote t move at all?\rdblquote  Ron sounded amazed. \i\ldblquote Weird!\rdblquote\i0\par
Harry stared as Dumbledore sidled back into the picture on his card and gave him a small smile. Ron was more interested in eating the frogs than looking at the Famous Witches and Wizards cards, but Harry couldn\rquote t keep his eyes off them. Soon he had not only Dumbledore and Morgana, but Hengist of Woodcraft, Alberic Grunnion, Circe, Paracelsus, and Merlin. He finally tore his eyes away from the druidess Cliodna, who was scratching her nose, to open a bag of Bertie Bott\rquote s Every Flavor Beans.\par
\ldblquote You want to be careful with those,\rdblquote  Ron warned Harry. \ldblquote When they say every flavor, they \i mean\i0  every flavor \emdash  you know, you get all the ordinary ones like chocolate and peppermint and marmalade, but then you can get spinach and liver and tripe. George reckons he had a booger-flavored one once.\rdblquote\par
Ron picked up a green bean, looked at it carefully, and bit into a corner.\par
\ldblquote Bleaaargh \emdash  see? Sprouts.\rdblquote\par
They had a good time eating the Every Flavor Beans. Harry got toast, coconut, baked bean, strawberry, curry, grass, coffee, sardine, and was even brave enough to nibble the end off a funny gray one Ron wouldn\rquote t touch, which turned out to be pepper.\par
The countryside now flying past the window was becoming wilder. The neat fields had gone. Now there were woods, twisting rivers, and dark green hills.\par
There was a knock on the door of their compartment and the round-faced boy Harry had passed on platform nine and three-quarters came in. He looked tearful.\par
\ldblquote Sorry,\rdblquote  he said, \ldblquote but have you seen a toad at all?\rdblquote\par
When they shook their heads, he wailed, \ldblquote I\rquote ve lost him! He keeps getting away from me!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote He\rquote ll turn up,\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said the boy miserably. \ldblquote Well, if you see him \'85\rdblquote\par
He left.\par
\ldblquote Don\rquote t know why he\rquote s so bothered,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote If I\rquote d brought a toad I\rquote d lose it as quick as I could. Mind you, I brought Scabbers, so I can\rquote t talk.\rdblquote\par
The rat was still snoozing on Ron\rquote s lap.\par
\ldblquote He might have died and you wouldn\rquote t know the difference,\rdblquote  said Ron in disgust. \ldblquote I tried to turn him yellow yesterday to make him more interesting, but the spell didn\rquote t work. I\rquote ll show you, look \'85\rdblquote\par
He rummaged around in his trunk and pulled out a very battered-looking wand. It was chipped in places and something white was glinting at the end.\par
\ldblquote Unicorn hair\rquote s nearly poking out. Anyway \emdash\rdblquote\par
