Turn this stupid, fat rat yellow.\rdblquote\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\i0\par
He waved his wand, but nothing happened. Scabbers stayed gray and fast asleep.\par
\ldblquote Are you sure that\rquote s a real spell?\rdblquote  said the girl. \ldblquote Well, it\rquote s not very good, is it? I\rquote ve tried a few simple spells just for practice and it\rquote s all worked for me. Nobody in my family\rquote s magic at all, it was ever such a surprise when I got my letter, but I was ever so pleased, of course, I mean, it\rquote s the very best school of witchcraft there is, I\rquote ve heard \emdash  I\rquote ve learned all our course books by heart, of course, I just hope it will be enough \emdash  I\rquote m Hermione Granger, by the way, who are you?\rdblquote\par
She said all this very fast.\par
Harry looked at Ron, and was relieved to see by his stunned face that he hadn\rquote t learned all the course books by heart either.\par
\ldblquote I\rquote m Ron Weasley,\rdblquote  Ron muttered.\par
\ldblquote Harry Potter,\rdblquote  said Harry.\par
\ldblquote Are you really?\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote I know all about you, of course \emdash  I got a few extra books for background reading, and you\rquote re in \i Modern Magical History\i0  and \i The Rise and Fall of the Dark Arts\i0  and \i Great Wizarding Events of the Twentieth Century.\rdblquote\i0\par
\ldblquote Am I?\rdblquote  said Harry, feeling dazed.\par
\ldblquote Goodness, didn\rquote t you know, I\rquote d have found out everything I could if it was me,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote Do either of you know what House you\rquote ll be in? I\rquote ve been asking around, and I hope I\rquote m in Gryffindor, it sounds by far the best; I hear Dumbledore himself was in it, but I suppose Ravenclaw wouldn\rquote t be too bad. \'85 Any\-way, we\rquote d better go and look for Neville\rquote s toad. You two had better change, you know, I expect we\rquote ll be there soon.\rdblquote\par
And she left, taking the toadless boy with her.\par
\ldblquote Whatever House I\rquote m in, I hope she\rquote s not in it,\rdblquote  said Ron. He threw his wand back into his trunk. \ldblquote Stupid spell \emdash  George gave it to me, bet he knew it was a dud.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What House are your brothers in?\rdblquote  asked Harry.\par
\ldblquote Gryffindor,\rdblquote  said Ron. Gloom seemed to be settling on him again. \ldblquote Mom and Dad were in it, too. I don\rquote t know what they\rquote ll say if I\rquote m not. I don\rquote t suppose Ravenclaw \i would\i0  be too bad, but imag\-ine if they put me in Slytherin.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote That\rquote s the House Vol-, I mean, You-Know-Who was in?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Ron. He flopped back into his seat, looking de\-pressed.\par
\ldblquote You know, I think the ends of Scabbers\rquote  whiskers are a bit lighter,\rdblquote  said Harry, trying to take Ron\rquote s mind off Houses. \ldblquote So what do your oldest brothers do now that they\rquote ve left, anyway?\rdblquote\par
Harry was wondering what a wizard did once he\rquote d finished school.\par
\ldblquote Charlie\rquote s in Romania studying dragons, and Bill\rquote s in Africa do\-ing something for Gringotts,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Did you hear about Gringotts? It\rquote s been all over the \i Daily Prophet,\i0  but I don\rquote t suppose you get that with the Muggles \emdash  someone tried to rob a high se\-curity vault.\rdblquote\par
Harry stared.\par
\ldblquote Really? What happened to them?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Nothing, that\rquote s why it\rquote s such big news. They haven\rquote t been caught. My dad says it must\rquote ve been a powerful Dark wizard to get round Gringotts, but they don\rquote t think they took anything, that\rquote s what\rquote s odd. \rquote Course, everyone gets scared when something like this happens in case You-Know-Who\rquote s behind it.\rdblquote\par
Harry turned this news over in his mind. He was starting to get a prickle of fear every time You-Know-Who was mentioned. He supposed this was all part of entering the magical world, but it had been a lot more comfortable saying \ldblquote Voldemort\rdblquote  without worrying.\par
\ldblquote What\rquote s your Quidditch team?\rdblquote  Ron asked.\par
\ldblquote Er \emdash  I don\rquote t know any,\rdblquote  Harry confessed.\par
\ldblquote What!\rdblquote  Ron looked dumbfounded. \ldblquote Oh, you wait, it\rquote s the best game in the world \emdash\rdblquote  And he was off, explaining all about the four balls and the positions of the seven players, describing famous games he\rquote d been to with his brothers and the broomstick he\rquote d like to get if he had the money. He was just taking Harry through the finer points of the game when the compartment door slid open yet again, but it wasn\rquote t Neville the toadless boy, or Hermione Granger this time.\par
Three boys entered, and Harry recognized the middle one at once: It was the pale boy from Madam Malkin\rquote s robe shop. He was looking at Harry with a lot more interest than he\rquote d shown back in Diagon Alley.\par
\ldblquote Is it true?\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote They\rquote re saying all down the train that Harry Potter\rquote s in this compartment. So it\rquote s you, is it?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Harry. He was looking at the other boys. Both of them were thickset and looked extremely mean. Standing on either side of the pale boy, they looked like bodyguards.\par
\ldblquote Oh, this is Crabbe and this is Goyle,\rdblquote  said the pale boy care\-lessly, noticing where Harry was looking. \ldblquote And my names Malfoy, Draco Malfoy.\rdblquote\par
Ron gave a slight cough, which might have been hiding a snig\-ger. Draco Malfoy looked at him.\par
\ldblquote Think my name\rquote s funny, do you? No need to ask who you are. My father told me all the Weasleys have red hair, freckles, and more children than they can afford.\rdblquote\par
He turned back to Harry. \ldblquote You\rquote ll soon find out some wizarding families are much better than others, Potter. You don\rquote t want to go making friends with the wrong sort. I can help you there.\rdblquote\par
He held out his hand to shake Harry\rquote s, but Harry didn\rquote t take it.\par
\ldblquote I think I can tell who the wrong sort are for myself, thanks,\rdblquote  he said coolly.\par
Draco Malfoy didn\rquote t go red, but a pink tinge appeared in his pale cheeks.\par
\ldblquote I\rquote d be careful if I were you, Potter,\rdblquote  he said slowly. \ldblquote Unless you\rquote re a bit politer you\rquote ll go the same way as your parents. They didn\rquote t know what was good for them, either. You hang around with riffraff like the Weasleys and that Hagrid, and it\rquote ll rub off on you.\rdblquote\par
Both Harry and Ron stood up.\par
\ldblquote Say that again,\rdblquote  Ron said, his face as red as his hair.\par
\ldblquote Oh, you\rquote re going to fight us, are you?\rdblquote  Malfoy sneered.\par
\ldblquote Unless you get out now,\rdblquote  said Harry, more bravely than he felt, because Crabbe and Goyle were a lot bigger than him or Ron.\par
\ldblquote But we don\rquote t feel like leaving, do we, boys? We\rquote ve eaten all our food and you still seem to have some.\rdblquote\par
Goyle reached toward the Chocolate Frogs next to Ron \emdash  Ron leapt forward, but before he\rquote d so much as touched Goyle, Goyle let out a horrible yell.\par
Scabbers the rat was hanging off his finger, sharp little teeth sunk deep into Goyle\rquote s knuckle \emdash  Crabbe and Malfoy backed away as Goyle swung Scabbers round and round, howling, and when Scab\-bers finally flew off and hit the window, all three of them disap\-peared at once. Perhaps they thought there were more rats lurking among the sweets, or perhaps they\rquote d heard footsteps, because a sec\-ond later, Hermione Granger had come in.\par
\ldblquote What \i has\i0  been going on?\rdblquote  she said, looking at the sweets all over the floor and Ron picking up Scabbers by his tail.\par
\ldblquote I think he\rquote s been knocked out,\rdblquote  Ron said to Harry. He looked closer at Scabbers. \ldblquote No \emdash  I don\rquote t believe it \emdash  he\rquote s gone back to sleep.\rdblquote\par
And so he had.\par
\ldblquote You\rquote ve met Malfoy before?\rdblquote\par
Harry explained about their meeting in Diagon Alley.\par
\ldblquote I\rquote ve heard of his family,\rdblquote  said Ron darkly. \ldblquote They were some of the first to come back to our side after You-Know-Who disap\-peared. Said they\rquote d been bewitched. My dad doesn\rquote t believe it. He says Malfoy\rquote s father didn\rquote t need an excuse to go over to the Dark Side.\rdblquote  He turned to Hermione. \ldblquote Can we help you with some\-thing?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote You\rquote d better hurry up and put your robes on, I\rquote ve just been up to the front to ask the conductor, and he says we\rquote re nearly there. You haven\rquote t been fighting, have you? You\rquote ll be in trouble before we even get there!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Scabbers has been fighting, not us,\rdblquote  said Ron, scowling at her. \ldblquote Would you mind leaving while we change?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote All right \emdash  I only came in here because people outside are be\-having very childishly, racing up and down the corridors,\rdblquote  said Hermione in a sniffy voice. \ldblquote And you\rquote ve got dirt on your nose, by the way, did you know?\rdblquote\par
Ron glared at her as she left. Harry peered out of the window. It was getting dark. He could see mountains and forests under a deep purple sky. The train did seem to be slowing down.\par
He and Ron took off their jackets and pulled on their long black robes. Ron\rquote s were a bit short for him, you could see his sneakers un\-derneath them.\par
A voice echoed through the train: \ldblquote We will be reaching Hogwarts in five minutes\rquote  time. Please leave your luggage on the train, it will be taken to the school separately.\rdblquote\par
Harry\rquote s stomach lurched with nerves and Ron, he saw, looked pale under his freckles. They crammed their pockets with the last of the sweets and joined the crowd thronging the corridor.\par
The train slowed right down and finally stopped. People pushed their way toward the door and out on to a tiny, dark platform. Harry shivered in the cold night air. Then a lamp came bobbing over the heads of the students, and Harry heard a familiar voice: \ldblquote Firs\rquote  years! Firs\rquote  years over here! All right there, Harry?\rdblquote\par
Hagrid\rquote s big hairy face beamed over the sea of heads.\par
\ldblquote C\rquote mon, follow me \emdash  any more firs\rquote  years? Mind yer step, now! Firs\rquote  years follow me!\rdblquote\par
Slipping and stumbling, they followed Hagrid down what seemed to be a steep, narrow path. It was so dark on either side of them that Harry thought there must be thick trees there. Nobody spoke much. Neville, the boy who kept losing his toad, sniffed once or twice.\par
\ldblquote Yeh\rquote ll get yer firs\rquote  sight o\rquote  Hogwarts in a sec,\rdblquote  Hagrid called over his shoulder, \ldblquote jus\rquote  round this bend here.\rdblquote\par
There was a loud \ldblquote Oooooh!\rdblquote\par
The narrow path had opened suddenly onto the edge of a great black lake. Perched atop a high mountain on the other side, its windows sparkling in the starry sky, was a vast castle with many turrets and towers.\par
\ldblquote No more\rquote n four to a boat!\rdblquote  Hagrid called, pointing to a fleet of little boats sitting in the water by the shore. Harry and Ron were followed into their boat by Neville and Hermione.\par
\ldblquote Everyone in?\rdblquote  shouted Hagrid, who had a boat to himself. \ldblquote Right then \emdash  FORWARD!\rdblquote\par
And the fleet of little boats moved off all at once, gliding across the lake, which was as smooth as glass. Everyone was silent, staring up at the great castle overhead. It towered over them as they sailed nearer and nearer to the cliff on which it stood.\par
\ldblquote Heads down!\rdblquote  yelled Hagrid as the first boats reached the cliff; they all bent their heads and the little boats carried them through a curtain of ivy that hid a wide opening in the cliff face. They were carried along a dark tunnel, which seemed to be taking them right underneath the castle, until they reached a kind of underground harbor, where they clambered out onto rocks and pebbles.\par
\ldblquote Oy, you there! Is this your toad?\rdblquote  said Hagrid, who was check\-ing the boats as people climbed out of them.\par
\ldblquote Trevor!\rdblquote  cried Neville blissfully, holding out his hands. Then they clambered up a passageway in the rock after Hagrid\rquote s lamp, coming out at last onto smooth, damp grass right in the shadow of the castle.\par
They walked up a flight of stone steps and crowded around the huge, oak front door.\par
\ldblquote Everyone here? You there, still got yer toad?\rdblquote\par
Hagrid raised a gigantic fist and knocked three times on the cas\-tle door.\par
