Ron stared after her, his mouth open.\par
\ldblquote No, we don\rquote t mind,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote You\rquote d think we dragged her along, wouldn\rquote t you?\rdblquote\par
But Hermione had given Harry something else to think about as he climbed back into bed. The dog was guarding something. \'85 What had Hagrid said? Gringotts was the safest place in the world for something you wanted to hide \emdash  except perhaps Hog\-warts.\par
It looked as though Harry had found out where the grubby lit\-tle package from vault seven hundred and thirteen was.\par
