\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj And there were his mother and father smiling at him again, and one of his grandfathers nodding happily. Harry sank down to sit on the floor in front of the mirror. There was nothing to stop him from staying here all night with his family. Nothing at all.\par
Except \emdash\par
\ldblquote So \emdash  back again, Harry?\rdblquote\par
Harry felt as though his insides had turned to ice. He looked be\-hind him. Sitting on one of the desks by the wall was none other than Albus Dumbledore. Harry must have walked straight past him, so desperate to get to the mirror he hadn\rquote t noticed him.\par
\ldblquote I \emdash  I didn\rquote t see you, sir.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Strange how nearsighted being invisible can make you,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, and Harry was relieved to see that he was smiling.\par
\ldblquote So,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, slipping off the desk to sit on the floor with Harry, \ldblquote you, like hundreds before you, have discovered the delights of the Mirror of Erised.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I didn\rquote t know it was called that, sir.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote But I expect you\rquote ve realized by now what it does?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote It \emdash  well \emdash  it shows me my family \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote And it showed your friend Ron himself as Head Boy.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote How did you know \emdash  ?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I don\rquote t need a cloak to become invisible,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore gently. \ldblquote Now, can you think what the Mirror of Erised shows us all?\rdblquote\par
Harry shook his head.\par
\ldblquote Let me explain. The happiest man on earth would be able to use the Mirror of Erised like a normal mirror, that is, he would look into it and see himself exactly as he is. Does that help?\rdblquote\par
Harry thought. Then he said slowly, \ldblquote It shows us what we want \'85 whatever we want \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yes and no,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore quietly. \ldblquote It shows us nothing more or less than the deepest, most desperate desire of our hearts. You, who have never known your family, see them standing around you. Ronald Weasley, who has always been overshadowed by his brothers, sees himself standing alone, the best of all of them. How\-ever, this mirror will give us neither knowledge or truth. Men have wasted away before it, entranced by what they have seen, or been driven mad, not knowing if what it shows is real or even possible.\par
\ldblquote The Mirror will be moved to a new home tomorrow, Harry, and I ask you not to go looking for it again. If you ever \i do \i0 run across it, you will now be prepared. It does not do to dwell on dreams and forget to live, remember that. Now, why don\rquote t you put that admirable cloak back on and get off to bed?\rdblquote\par
Harry stood up.\par
\ldblquote Sir \emdash  Professor Dumbledore? Can I ask you something?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Obviously, you\rquote ve just done so,\rdblquote  Dumbledore smiled. \ldblquote You may ask me one more thing, however.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What do you see when you look in the mirror?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I? I see myself holding a pair of thick, woolen socks.\rdblquote\par
Harry stared.\par
\ldblquote One can never have enough socks,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote An\-other Christmas has come and gone and I didn\rquote t get a single pair. People will insist on giving me books.\rdblquote\par
It was only when he was back in bed that it struck Harry that Dumbledore might not have been quite truthful. But then, he thought, as he shoved Scabbers off his pillow, it had been quite a personal question.\par
