\pard\nowidctlpar\qj In years to come, Harry would never quite remember how he had managed to get through his exams when he half expected Voldemort to come bursting through the door at any moment. Yet the days crept by, and there could be no doubt that Fluffy was still alive and well behind the locked door.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj It was sweltering hot, especially in the large classroom where they did their written papers. They had been given special, new quills for the exams, which had been bewitched with an Anti-Cheating spell.\par
They had practical exams as well. Professor Flitwick called them one by one into his class to see if they could make a pineapple tap-dance across a desk. Professor McGonagall watched them turn a mouse into a snuffbox \emdash  points were given for how pretty the snuffbox was, but taken away if it had whiskers. Snape made them all nervous, breathing down their necks while they tried to remem\-ber how to make a Forgetfulness potion.\par
Harry did the best he could, trying to ignore the stabbing pains in his forehead, which had been bothering him ever since his trip into the forest. Neville thought Harry had a bad case of exam nerves because Harry couldn\rquote t sleep, but the truth was that Harry kept being woken by his old nightmare, except that it was now worse than ever because there was a hooded figure dripping blood in it.\par
Maybe it was because they hadn\rquote t seen what Harry had seen in the forest, or because they didn\rquote t have scars burning on their fore\-heads, but Ron and Hermione didn\rquote t seem as worried about the Stone as Harry. The idea of Voldemort certainly scared them, but he didn\rquote t keep visiting them in dreams, and they were so busy with their studying they didn\rquote t have much time to fret about what Snape or anyone else might be up to.\par
Their very last exam was History of Magic. One hour of an\-swering questions about batty old wizards who\rquote d invented self-stirring cauldrons and they\rquote d be free, free for a whole wonderful week until their exam results came out. When the ghost of Profes\-sor Binns told them to put down their quills and roll up their parchment, Harry couldn\rquote t help cheering with the rest.\par
\ldblquote That was far easier than I thought it would be,\rdblquote  said Hermione as they joined the crowds flocking out onto the sunny grounds. \ldblquote I needn\rquote t have learned about the 1637 Werewolf Code of Conduct or the uprising of Elfric the Eager.\rdblquote\par
Hermione always liked to go through their exam papers after\-ward, but Ron said this made him feel ill, so they wandered down to the lake and flopped under a tree. The Weasley twins and Lee Jordan were tickling the tentacles of a giant squid, which was bask\-ing in the warm shallows.\par
\ldblquote No more studying,\rdblquote  Ron sighed happily, stretching out on the grass. \ldblquote You could look more cheerful, Harry, we\rquote ve got a week be\-fore we find out how badly we\rquote ve done, there\rquote s no need to worry yet.\rdblquote\par
Harry was rubbing his forehead.\par
\ldblquote I wish I knew what this \i means!\rdblquote\i0  he burst out angrily. \ldblquote My scar keeps hurting \emdash  it\rquote s happened before, but never as often as this.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Go to Madam Pomfrey,\rdblquote  Hermione suggested.\par
\ldblquote I\rquote m not ill,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote I think it\rquote s a warning \'85 it means danger\rquote s coming. \'85\rdblquote\par
Ron couldn\rquote t get worked up, it was too hot.\par
\ldblquote Harry, relax, Hermione\rquote s right, the Stone\rquote s safe as long as Dum\-bledore\rquote s around. Anyway, we\rquote ve never had any proof Snape found out how to get past Fluffy. He nearly had his leg ripped off once, he\rquote s not going to try it again in a hurry. And Neville will play Quid\-ditch for England before Hagrid lets Dumbledore down.\rdblquote\par
Harry nodded, but he couldn\rquote t shake off a lurking feeling that there was something he\rquote d forgotten to do, something important. When he tried to explain this, Hermione said, \ldblquote That\rquote s just the ex\-ams. I woke up last night and was halfway through my Transfigu\-ration notes before I remembered we\rquote d done that one.\rdblquote\par
Harry was quite sure the unsettled feeling didn\rquote t have anything to do with work, though. He watched an owl flutter toward the school across the bright blue sky, a note clamped in its mouth. Ha\-grid was the only one who ever sent him letters. Hagrid would never betray Dumbledore. Hagrid would never tell anyone how to get past Fluffy \'85 never \'85 but \emdash\par
Harry suddenly jumped to his feet.\par
\ldblquote Where\rquote re you going?\rdblquote  said Ron sleepily.\par
\ldblquote I\rquote ve just thought of something,\rdblquote  said Harry. He had turned white. \ldblquote We\rquote ve got to go and see Hagrid, now.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Why?\rdblquote  panted Hermione, hurrying to keep up.\par
\ldblquote Don\rquote t you think it\rquote s a bit odd,\rdblquote  said Harry, scrambling up the grassy slope, \ldblquote that what Hagrid wants more than anything else is a dragon, and a stranger turns up who just happens to have an egg in his pocket? How many people wander around with dragon eggs if it\rquote s against wizard law? Lucky they found Hagrid, don\rquote t you think? Why didn\rquote t I see it before?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What are you talking about?\rdblquote  said Ron, but Harry, sprinting across the grounds toward the forest, didn\rquote t answer.\par
Hagrid was sitting in an armchair outside his house; his trousers and sleeves were rolled up, and he was shelling peas into a large bowl.\par
\ldblquote Hullo,\rdblquote  he said, smiling. \ldblquote Finished yer exams? Got time fer a drink?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yes, please,\rdblquote  said Ron, but Harry cut him off.\par
\ldblquote No, we\rquote re in a hurry. Hagrid, I\rquote ve got to ask you something. You know that night you won Norbert? What did the stranger you were playing cards with look like?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Dunno,\rdblquote  said Hagrid casually, \ldblquote he wouldn\rquote  take his cloak off.\rdblquote\par
He saw the three of them look stunned and raised his eye\-brows.\par
\ldblquote It\rquote s not that unusual, yeh get a lot o\rquote  funny folk in the Hog\rquote s Head \emdash  that\rquote s one o\rquote  the pubs down in the village. Mighta bin a dragon dealer, mightn\rquote  he? I never saw his face, he kept his hood up.\rdblquote\par
Harry sank down next to the bowl of peas.\par
\ldblquote What did you talk to him about, Hagrid? Did you mention Hogwarts at all?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Mighta come up,\rdblquote  said Hagrid, frowning as he tried to remem\-ber. \ldblquote Yeah \'85 he asked what I did, an\rquote  I told him I was gamekeeper here. \'85 He asked a bit about the sorta creatures I look after \'85 so I told him \'85 an\rquote  I said what I\rquote d always really wanted was a dragon \'85 an\rquote  then \'85 I can\rquote  remember too well, \rquote cause he kept buyin\rquote  me drinks. \'85 Let\rquote s see \'85 yeah, then he said he had the dragon egg an\rquote  we could play cards fer it if I wanted \'85 but he had ter be sure I could handle it, he didn\rquote  want it ter go ter any old home. \'85 So I told him, after Fluffy, a dragon would be easy. \'85\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote And did he \emdash  did he seem interested in Fluffy?\rdblquote  Harry asked, trying to keep his voice calm.\par
\ldblquote Well \emdash  yeah \emdash  how many three-headed dogs d\rquote yeh meet, even around Hogwarts? So I told him, Fluffy\rquote s a piece o\rquote  cake if yeh know how to calm him down, jus\rquote  play him a bit o\rquote  music an\rquote  he\rquote ll go straight off ter sleep \emdash\rdblquote\par
Hagrid suddenly looked horrified.\par
\ldblquote I shouldn\rquote ta told yeh that!\rdblquote  he blurted out. \ldblquote Forget I said it! Hey \emdash  where\rquote re yeh goin\rquote ?\rdblquote\par
Harry, Ron, and Hermione didn\rquote t speak to each other at all un\-til they came to a halt in the entrance hall, which seemed very cold and gloomy after the grounds.\par
\ldblquote We\rquote ve got to go to Dumbledore,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Hagrid told that stranger how to get past Fluffy, and it was either Snape or Volde\-mort under that cloak \emdash  it must\rquote ve been easy, once he\rquote d got Ha\-grid drunk. I just hope Dumbledore believes us. Firenze might back us up if Bane doesn\rquote t stop him. Where\rquote s Dumbledore\rquote s office?\rdblquote\par
They looked around, as if hoping to see a sign pointing them in the right direction. They had never been told where Dumbledore lived, nor did they know anyone who had been sent to see him.\par
\ldblquote We\rquote ll just have to \emdash\rdblquote  Harry began, but a voice suddenly rang across the hall.\par
\ldblquote What are you three doing inside?\rdblquote\par
It was Professor McGonagall, carrying a large pile of books.\par
\ldblquote We want to see Professor Dumbledore,\rdblquote  said Hermione, rather bravely, Harry and Ron thought.\par
\ldblquote See Professor Dumbledore?\rdblquote  Professor McGonagall repeated, as though this was a very fishy thing to want to do. \ldblquote Why?\rdblquote\par
Harry swallowed \emdash  now what?\par
\ldblquote It\rquote s sort of secret,\rdblquote  he said, but he wished at once he hadn\rquote t, be\-cause Professor McGonagall\rquote s nostrils flared.\par
\ldblquote Professor Dumbledore left ten minutes ago,\rdblquote  she said coldly. \ldblquote He received an urgent owl from the Ministry of Magic and flew off for London at once.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote He\rquote s \i gone?\rdblquote\i0  said Harry frantically. \i\ldblquote Now?\rdblquote\i0\par
\ldblquote Professor Dumbledore is a very great wizard, Potter, he has many demands on his time \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote But this is important.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Something you have to say is more important than the Min\-istry of Magic, Potter?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Look,\rdblquote  said Harry, throwing caution to the winds, \ldblquote Pro\-fessor \emdash  it\rquote s about the Sorcerer\rquote s Stone \emdash\rdblquote\par
Whatever Professor McGonagall had expected, it wasn\rquote t that. The books she was carrying tumbled out of her arms, but she didn\rquote t pick them up.\par
\ldblquote How do you know \emdash  ?\rdblquote  she spluttered.\par
\ldblquote Professor, I think \emdash  I \i know\i0  \emdash  that Sn\emdash  that someone\rquote s going to try and steal the Stone. I\rquote ve got to talk to Professor Dumble\-dore.\rdblquote\par
She eyed him with a mixture of shock and suspicion.\par
\ldblquote Professor Dumbledore will be back tomorrow,\rdblquote  she said finally. \ldblquote I don\rquote t know how you found out about the Stone, but rest assured, no one can possibly steal it, it\rquote s too well protected.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote But Professor \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Potter, I know what I\rquote m talking about,\rdblquote  she said shortly. She bent down and gathered up the fallen books. \ldblquote I suggest you all go back outside and enjoy the sunshine.\rdblquote\par
But they didn\rquote t.\par
\ldblquote It\rquote s tonight,\rdblquote  said Harry, once he was sure Professor McGona\-gall was out of earshot. \ldblquote Snape\rquote s going through the trapdoor tonight. He\rquote s found out everything he needs, and now he\rquote s got Dumbledore out of the way. He sent that note, I bet the Ministry of Magic will get a real shock when Dumbledore turns up.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote But what can we \emdash\rdblquote\par
Hermione gasped. Harry and Ron wheeled round.\par
Snape was standing there.\par
\ldblquote Good afternoon,\rdblquote  he said smoothly.\par
They stared at him.\par
\ldblquote You shouldn\rquote t be inside on a day like this,\rdblquote  he said, with an odd, twisted smile.\par
\ldblquote We were \emdash\rdblquote  Harry began, without any idea what he was going to say.\par
\ldblquote You want to be more careful,\rdblquote  said Snape. \ldblquote Hanging around like this, people will think you\rquote re up to something. And Gryffindor really can\rquote t afford to lose any more points, can it?\rdblquote\par
Harry flushed. They turned to go outside, but Snape called them back.\par
\ldblquote Be warned, Potter \emdash  any more nighttime wanderings and I will personally make sure you are expelled. Good day to you.\rdblquote\par
