Out on the stone steps, Harry turned to the others.\par
\ldblquote Right, here\rquote s what we\rquote ve got to do,\rdblquote  he whispered urgently. \ldblquote One of us has got to keep an eye on Snape \emdash  wait outside the staffroom and follow him if he leaves it. Hermione, you\rquote d better do that.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Why me?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote It\rquote s obvious,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote You can pretend to be waiting for Professor Flitwick, you know.\rdblquote  He put on a high voice, \ldblquote  \lquote Oh Profes\-sor Flitwick, I\rquote m so worried, I think I got question fourteen \i b \i0 wrong. \'85\rquote  \rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Oh, shut up,\rdblquote  said Hermione, but she agreed to go and watch out for Snape.\par
\ldblquote And we\rquote d better stay outside the third-floor corridor,\rdblquote  Harry told Ron. \ldblquote Come on.\rdblquote\par
