\pard\nowidctlpar\qj After dinner the three of them sat nervously apart in the common room. Nobody bothered them; none of the Gryffindors had any\-thing to say to Harry any more, after all. This was the first night he hadn\rquote t been upset by it. Hermione was skimming through all her notes, hoping to come across one of the enchantments they were about to try to break. Harry and Ron didn\rquote t talk much. Both of them were thinking about what they were about to do.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj Slowly, the room emptied as people drifted off to bed.\par
\ldblquote Better get the cloak,\rdblquote  Ron muttered, as Lee Jordan finally left, stretching and yawning. Harry ran upstairs to their dark dormi\-tory. He pulled out the cloak and then his eyes fell on the flute Ha\-grid had given him for Christmas. He pocketed it to use on Fluffy \emdash  he didn\rquote t feel much like singing.\par
He ran back down to the common room.\par
\ldblquote We\rquote d better put the cloak on here, and make sure it covers all three of us \emdash  if Filch spots one of our feet wandering along on its own \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote What are you doing?\rdblquote  said a voice from the corner of the room. Neville appeared from behind an armchair, clutching Trevor the toad, who looked as though he\rquote d been making another bid for free\-dom.\par
\ldblquote Nothing, Neville, nothing,\rdblquote  said Harry, hurriedly putting the cloak behind his back.\par
Neville stared at their guilty faces.\par
\ldblquote You\rquote re going out again,\rdblquote  he said.\par
\ldblquote No, no, no,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote No, we\rquote re not. Why don\rquote t you go to bed, Neville?\rdblquote\par
Harry looked at the grandfather clock by the door. They couldn\rquote t afford to waste any more time, Snape might even now be playing Fluffy to sleep.\par
\ldblquote You can\rquote t go out,\rdblquote  said Neville, \ldblquote you\rquote ll be caught again. Gryffindor will be in even more trouble.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote You don\rquote t understand,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote this is important.\rdblquote\par
But Neville was clearly steeling himself to do something desper\-ate.\par
\ldblquote I won\rquote t let you do it,\rdblquote  he said, hurrying to stand in front of the portrait hole. \ldblquote I\rquote ll \emdash  I\rquote ll fight you!\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote Neville,\rdblquote\i0  Ron exploded, \ldblquote get away from that hole and don\rquote t be an idiot \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Don\rquote t you call me an idiot!\rdblquote  said Neville. \ldblquote I don\rquote t think you should be breaking any more rules! And you were the one who told me to stand up to people!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Yes, but not to \i us,\i0\rdblquote  said Ron in exasperation. \ldblquote Neville, you don\rquote t know what you\rquote re doing.\rdblquote\par
He took a step forward and Neville dropped Trevor the toad, who leapt out of sight.\par
\ldblquote Go on then, try and hit me!\rdblquote  said Neville, raising his fists. \ldblquote I\rquote m ready!\rdblquote\par
Harry turned to Hermione.\par
\i\ldblquote Do something,\rdblquote\i0  he said desperately.\par
Hermione stepped forward.\par
\ldblquote Neville,\rdblquote  she said, \ldblquote I\rquote m really, really sorry about this.\rdblquote\par
She raised her wand.\par
\i\ldblquote Petrificus Totalus!\rdblquote\i0  she cried, pointing it at Neville.\par
Neville\rquote s arms snapped to his sides. His legs sprang together. His whole body rigid, he swayed where he stood and then fell flat on his face, stiff as a board.\par
Hermione ran to turn him over. Neville\rquote s jaws were jammed to\-gether so he couldn\rquote t speak. Only his eyes were moving, looking at them in horror.\par
\ldblquote What\rquote ve you done to him?\rdblquote  Harry whispered.\par
