\pard\nowidctlpar\qj It was Quirrell. \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\i\ldblquote You!\rdblquote\i0  gasped Harry.\par
Quirrell smiled. His face wasn\rquote t twitching at all.\par
\ldblquote Me,\rdblquote  he said calmly. \ldblquote I wondered whether I\rquote d be meeting you here, Potter.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote But I thought \emdash  Snape \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Severus?\rdblquote  Quirrell laughed, and it wasn\rquote t his usual quivering treble, either, but cold and sharp. \ldblquote Yes, Severus does seem the type, doesn\rquote t he? So useful to have him swooping around like an over\-grown bat. Next to him, who would suspect p-p-poor, st-stuttering P-Professor Quirrell?\rdblquote\par
Harry couldn\rquote t take it in. This couldn\rquote t be true, it couldn\rquote t.\par
\ldblquote But Snape tried to kill me!\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote No, no, no. \i I\i0  tried to kill you. Your friend Miss Granger acci\-dentally knocked me over as she rushed to set fire to Snape at that Quidditch match. She broke my eye contact with you. Another few seconds and I\rquote d have got you off that broom. I\rquote d have managed it before then if Snape hadn\rquote t been muttering a countercurse, try\-ing to save you.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Snape was trying to \i save\i0  me?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Of course,\rdblquote  said Quirrell coolly. \ldblquote Why do you think he wanted to referee your next match? He was trying to make sure I didn\rquote t do it again. Funny, really \'85 he needn\rquote t have bothered. I couldn\rquote t do anything with Dumbledore watching. All the other teachers thought Snape was trying to stop Gryffindor from winning, he \i did \i0 make himself unpopular \'85 and what a waste of time, when after all that, I\rquote m going to kill you tonight.\rdblquote\par
Quirrell snapped his fingers. Ropes sprang out of thin air and wrapped themselves tightly around Harry.\par
\ldblquote You\rquote re too nosy to live, Potter. Scurrying around the school on Halloween like that, for all I knew you\rquote d seen me coming to look at what was guarding the Stone.\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote You\i0  let the troll in?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Certainly. I have a special gift with trolls \emdash  you must have seen what I did to the one in the chamber back there? Unfortunately, while everyone else was running around looking for it, Snape, who already suspected me, went straight to the third floor to head me off \emdash  and not only did my troll fail to beat you to death, that three-headed dog didn\rquote t even manage to bite Snape\rquote s leg off properly.\par
\ldblquote Now, wait quietly, Potter. I need to examine this interesting mirror.\rdblquote\par
It was only then that Harry realized what was standing behind Quirrell. It was the Mirror of Erised.\par
\ldblquote This mirror is the key to finding the Stone,\rdblquote  Quirrell mur\-mured, tapping his way around the frame. \ldblquote Trust Dumbledore to come up with something like this \'85 but he\rquote s in London \'85 I\rquote ll be far away by the time he gets back. \'85\rdblquote\par
All Harry could think of doing was to keep Quirrell talking and stop him from concentrating on the mirror.\par
\ldblquote I saw you and Snape in the forest \emdash\rdblquote  he blurted out.\par
\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Quirrell idly, walking around the mirror to look at the back. \ldblquote He was on to me by that time, trying to find out how far I\rquote d got. He suspected me all along. Tried to frighten me \emdash  as though he could, when I had Lord Voldemort on my side. \'85\rdblquote\par
Quirrell came back out from behind the mirror and stared hun\-grily into it.\par
\ldblquote I see the Stone \'85 I\rquote m presenting it to my master \'85 but where is it?\rdblquote\par
